rez.biog:
Mixcloud co-founder, DJ, designer, entrepreneur, speaker, and BBoy. Born in Paris, grew up in Philly and Brussels and now based in London. 

Radio and mixtape fiend since the age of 14.

For bookings please contact: dj (at) nicoperez (dot) com
Make music? Send sounds to: beats (at) nicoperez (dot) com

cloudcasts.name: Tropical Snow
cloudcasts.description: I finally stopped designing and coding this site long enough to make my own Cloudcast mix and upload it. The vibes are tropical - like a warm caribbean island - with a more b-more/dance swing in the second half. Inspired by Summertime Stonebridge Park pirate radio, coconut water, the We-make-it-good mix series, and Mr John Peel. Big up to everyone who's helped make this site possible, and thanks for all the great content that people have put up.

cloudcasts.name: Mixcloud It's Your Birthday
cloudcasts.description:
Time really does fly when you're having fun. I remember 21 September 2009 so clearly - massive countdown timer on the site, phones off the hook, and somehow topping the Twitter trending list with no less than 4 topics!

Without sounding cliched, the past 12 months have been a rollercoaster. Lots of fun & good times, plenty of challenges & lessons learned.

We're all so proud to have built such a fantastic, creative community - thank you all for being involved. I'm also honoured to have worked with so many inspiring people and companies over the past 12 months - thank you for sharing our vision and supporting the project.

This is my Birthday Mix to Mixcloud, including many tracks & artists discovered directly or indirectly through the site, e.g.

Amede & The Soundsmith via Laid Back
Lunice and TOKiMONSTA via RBMA Radio
Throwing Snow via Jus Like Music
Roska's Squark via Bleep
Busi Mhlongo via DJ Umb

Thank you beloved Mixclouders. Bring on Year 2 ;)

cloudcasts.name: This Is The Way We Dance
cloudcasts.description: A 45 minute mix of some of the beautiful and rhythmic house music I'm feeling at the moment - old and new. Deep synth tones to move your heart, off-centre drum grooves to move your ass.
